I think it would be less hassle to have a single assignment to the default value. We can drop the one before `config_get_value()`, and also drop this `buffer_size_str != NULL` test from the error condition, leaving:

```
buffer_size_str = config_get_value(config, "ringbuffer-size");
rc = config_parse_ringbuffer_size(buffer_size_str, &buffer_size);
if (rc) {
    buffer_size = default_buffer_size;
    ...
}
console->rb = ringbuffer_init(buffer_size);
```

It can be implemented like this:

```
size_t buffer_size = default_buffer_size;
...
buffer_size_str = config_get_value(config, "ringbuffer-size");
if (buffer_size_str) {
    rc = config_parse_bytesize(buffer_size_str, &buffer_size);
    if (rc) {
        warn("...");
    }
}```
